Tokuyama to Spend $135 Million to Build Polysilicon Plant in Yamaguchi

-- B y   G o   O n o m i t s u
-- 
2011-05-12T02:11:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-12/tokuyama-to-spend-135-million-to-build-polysilicon-plant-in-yamaguchi.html
Tokuyama Corp. (4043)  will invest 11 billion
yen ($135 million) to build a plant in Yamaguchi prefecture,
western  Japan , to raise production capacity of polysilicon.  Tokuyama expects to complete construction of the plant in
the first half of 2013, the Japanese industrial chemicals maker
said in a statement to the Tokyo Stock Exchange today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Go Onomitsu in Tokyo at 
 gonomitsu@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gearoid Reidy at 
 greidy1@bloomberg.net  